Group Wedding Held for Border Policemen on Pamir Plateau
Five couples tie the knot in a group wedding held in front of the No. 7 boundary demarcation at the Khunjerab Pass of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region on July 30, 2014. Five grooms, who are border military officers in the Khunjerab Frontier Defence Force, marry their respective brides, who are all from inner Chinese cities. [Photo: Imagine China]
Five couples got married on Wednesday in a group wedding held at the Khunjerab Pass in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
The five grooms, who have guarded the China-Pakistan border for many years, finally tied the knot with their respective brides from inner Chinese cities.
A solemnization was also held at the 5,100-meter mountain pass on the Pamir Plateau.Â 